From: Michael Chan <mchan@broadcom.com>
Date: Thu, 14 Feb 2013 12:13:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 009/108] tg3: Fix 5762 NVRAM sizing
Patch-mainline: v3.9-rc1
Git-commit: c5d0b72e641340c5dc915cdfab5e2c55d81425c2
References: bsc#908458 FATE#317507


Don't set the default size to 128K if it is 5762.  Instead, rely on the
size we obtain from NVRAM location 0xf0.

Signed-off-by: Michael Chan <mchan@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Cho, Yu-Chen <acho@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c |    6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c
@@ -13928,7 +13928,8 @@ static void tg3_get_5720_nvram_info(stru
 			tp->nvram_size = TG3_NVRAM_SIZE_1MB;
 			break;
 		default:
-			tp->nvram_size = TG3_NVRAM_SIZE_128KB;
+			if (GET_ASIC_REV(tp->pci_chip_rev_id) != ASIC_REV_5762)
+				tp->nvram_size = TG3_NVRAM_SIZE_128KB;
 			break;
 		}
 		break;
@@ -13974,7 +13975,8 @@ static void tg3_get_5720_nvram_info(stru
 			tp->nvram_size = TG3_NVRAM_SIZE_1MB;
 			break;
 		default:
-			tp->nvram_size = TG3_NVRAM_SIZE_128KB;
+			if (GET_ASIC_REV(tp->pci_chip_rev_id) != ASIC_REV_5762)
+				tp->nvram_size = TG3_NVRAM_SIZE_128KB;
 			break;
 		}
 		break;
